  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 03:15 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL signal engine is alive; notional is the blocker, not filters\n\n**Task:** Audit HL signal-generation logs since the live bot restart and decide whether the current Bollinger/volume filters are too strict, appropriate, or need a paper-only scoring layer while execution remains notional-blocked.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- HL live bot has been running since restart at `2026-05-03 02:17:49 UTC`.\n- Current live state: `execution_mode=notional_blocked`, balance `$37.391639`, planned order notional `$11.217492`, min order notional `$20.00`, positions `0`, current signals `0`.\n- Log audit since restart: **54** parsed recent lines, **19** cycle snapshots, **1** signal cycle, max signals in a cycle **1**, and **20** repeated skip logs over a ~4.5 minute signal window.\n- The only detected valid signal was **SHORT TRUMP**, skipped because notional was `$11.22` vs min `$20.00`.\n- No ERROR/WARNING pattern showed signal engine failure in the inspected post-restart window.\n- Current signal logic is already deliberately selective: BB period `20`, BB std `2.0`, base volume threshold `1.5x`, local RANGE requires at least `2.2x` volume plus `0.25%` breakout and sufficient band width, local MIXED requires `1.8x` volume plus `0.15%` breakout.\n- Notional math confirms blocker: `$37.39 * 10% * 3x = $11.22`; meeting `$20` at 10% margin and 3x needs about `$66.67`; using current balance at 3x would require ~17.8% capital margin and violate the 10% capital rule.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-hl-signal-generation-audit-since-restart-2026-05-03-0315.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The signal engine is not dead and is not obviously over-filtered. It produced one valid post-restart signal, and that signal was blocked only by notional. Loosening filters would mainly create more unexecutable signals while HL remains below the notional threshold.\n\n**Decision:** Keep HL live bot running. Keep `max_position_pct=0.10`, `leverage=3`, and `min_order_notional_usd=20.0` unchanged. Do not force trades from the `$37.39` wallet. Do not loosen BB/volume filters based on one blocked TRUMP short. Next useful P3 build is a paper-only signal ledger for pass/filtered/blocked signals with reason, local regime, vol ratio, breakout %, and forward returns.\n\n**Next:** Implement or spec the paper signal ledger. It should preserve live no-trade behavior while collecting data on whether filtered BB breakouts would have worked, especially in current `sentiment_impulse_up + expanding` macro context.\n\n## 2026-05-03 03:10 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Built 20 UTC alpha-outcome analyzer, confirmed current data gap\n\n**Task:** Build/verify the 20 UTC-specific analysis path requested after the alpha-overlay data gap: use realized `confidence_outcomes.jsonl` rows only when they carry `alpha_*` attribution, and avoid inf",
